WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.300
When it comes to really, really stupid reporting by mainstream media publications,

00:04.760 --> 00:10.160
the well runs kind of deep. You've got the pangolin wet market theory around COVID's origins,

00:10.460 --> 00:15.700
the whole Saddam Hussein had WMDs thing, the suppression of the Hunter Biden laptop story,

00:15.880 --> 00:20.440
calling ivermectin horse dewormer when hundreds of millions of people take it a year.

00:20.840 --> 00:25.860
I could go on for many days. But the Wall Street Journal just released an article called

00:25.860 --> 00:32.220
the Pentagon disinformation that fueled America's UFO mythology that truly takes the cake.

00:34.180 --> 00:38.100
I have to say, I agree with aspects of the headline.

00:38.440 --> 00:41.800
The Pentagon is running a UFO disinformation campaign.

00:42.200 --> 00:46.180
I think this article is part of that disinformation campaign.

00:48.180 --> 00:54.500
One of the article's primary sources is Susan Goff, whose own LinkedIn, along with independent sources,

00:54.500 --> 01:00.720
confirms her lead role in Booz Allen Hamilton's psychological operations consulting practice

01:00.720 --> 01:02.360
for the Department of Defense.

01:02.940 --> 01:07.500
Her self-professed skills include strategic communication and psychological operations.

01:12.500 --> 01:17.500
In summary, this article says that UFOs are entirely explained by two things.

01:17.500 --> 01:24.680
Electromagnetic pulses, or EMPs, that the American government secretly decided to use on our own

01:24.680 --> 01:27.340
nuclear missiles and Air Force hazing rituals.

01:27.720 --> 01:29.900
All right, you little freshman bitches!

01:30.700 --> 01:32.320
Let's tackle the first one.

01:35.500 --> 01:38.040
Good afternoon, my name is Robert Salas.

01:38.040 --> 01:46.220
On March 24th, 1967, Robert Salas, a first lieutenant stationed at Malmstrom Air Force Base, said he

01:46.220 --> 01:51.960
received a call from topside guards saying that they had seen strange lights in the sky making

01:51.960 --> 01:52.900
odd maneuvers.

01:54.320 --> 01:58.340
The men are stationed in the missile launch bunker 60 feet below ground.

01:59.340 --> 02:01.920
He called back about five minutes later.

02:01.920 --> 02:09.780
This time he was screaming into the phone saying they're looking at an object, a red glowing object

02:09.780 --> 02:12.440
hovering just above our front gate.

02:13.220 --> 02:14.840
All ten missiles were off alert.

02:14.940 --> 02:15.340
All ten.

02:16.020 --> 02:17.140
Whole flight was off alert.

02:17.380 --> 02:17.820
All red.

02:18.280 --> 02:24.020
Salas even had a colleague present named Bob Jameson, who backed up his testimony on record

02:24.020 --> 02:24.840
with Larry King.

02:25.020 --> 02:27.060
Is it possible they just malfunctioned?

02:27.240 --> 02:28.100
That doesn't happen.

02:28.100 --> 02:30.680
Very rarely does a missile malfunction.

02:30.940 --> 02:34.420
Much more rare would be two at the same time, but never ten.

02:34.880 --> 02:41.560
In fact, the guy who most thoroughly documents the Malmstrom case in 1967 is the author of the

02:41.560 --> 02:43.600
great book UFOs and Nukes.

02:43.980 --> 02:50.840
His name is Robert Hastings, and he is the authoritative chronicler of 167 Q-cleared nuclear

02:50.840 --> 02:54.320
base employees that have all witnessed UFOs.

02:54.320 --> 03:03.360
Declassified U.S. government documents and witness testimony from former or retired U.S.

03:03.360 --> 03:11.940
military personnel confirm beyond any doubt the reality of ongoing UFO incursions at nuclear

03:11.940 --> 03:13.040
weapons sites.

03:13.040 --> 03:18.280
In many cases, these UFOs have tampered with various nuclear sites across the country.

03:18.920 --> 03:23.680
Strangely enough, Bob Hastings figured out the connection between UFOs and nuclear weapons

03:23.680 --> 03:27.960
because his father was stationed at Malmstrom nuclear base in 1967.

03:28.620 --> 03:34.160
In high school, Hastings worked as a janitor there, and a radar operator who took young Hastings

03:34.160 --> 03:39.860
under his wing called the 16-year-old over to show him that the base was actually tracking

03:39.860 --> 03:42.200
what they called unknowns at the time.

03:42.200 --> 03:45.840
That's the formal term for unidentified objects.

03:46.400 --> 03:51.120
I saw five blips in the sort of northeast quadrant of his radar scope.

03:53.700 --> 04:00.300
A local truck driver in Montana and police officer are also on record having seen the UFO in the

04:00.300 --> 04:00.640
area.

04:01.240 --> 04:07.460
In 1993, a missile technician named John Mills stationed at Malmstrom also saw UFOs on his

04:07.460 --> 04:08.460
way back to the base.

04:08.960 --> 04:12.820
When he returned, officers there said the base had been swarmed.

04:13.180 --> 04:16.180
There are tons of sightings in and around Malmstrom.

04:16.180 --> 04:21.420
On the UFO thing, I was working for the Forest Service, not too far from Malmstrom Air Force Base.

04:21.740 --> 04:27.860
One day, I was up there in a Forest Service pickup truck at a certain campground, and I was there,

04:27.980 --> 04:31.660
and suddenly, I look up, and I say suddenly.

04:31.780 --> 04:32.820
It was just in the skies.

04:33.320 --> 04:35.720
I became aware that it was up there, and I looked up.

04:35.720 --> 04:43.280
It was this huge, spheroidal, you know, but elliptical, not a perfect spheroid, like a saucer

04:43.280 --> 04:45.020
that was turned partially on its side.

04:45.220 --> 04:46.840
These occur to this day.

04:46.840 --> 04:54.240
So anyways, this Wall Street Journal reporter named Joel Schechtman writes that this was

04:54.240 --> 05:00.960
all a secret EMP, or electromagnetic pulse experiment, seeing if the U.S. could shut down

05:00.960 --> 05:07.100
our own nukes with people present, as if that's not incredibly dangerous and reckless and has

05:07.100 --> 05:07.840
any precedent.

05:08.360 --> 05:12.000
I think that Schechtman, or one of his sources, is making this up.

05:12.000 --> 05:17.220
There's even documentation from Malmstrom Strategic Air Command itself, saying that they

05:17.220 --> 05:21.440
were extremely puzzled around the event, and that they had no idea what was going on.

05:21.720 --> 05:26.160
They were so puzzled that they paid Boeing to come out and investigate what had happened.

05:26.380 --> 05:27.660
Boeing was also puzzled.

05:29.400 --> 05:34.740
So again, back to this idea that this was a super secret EMP that no one knew about, and

05:34.740 --> 05:39.280
it was an EMP tested on our own nuclear weapons with people present.

05:39.280 --> 05:41.520
Bob Salas responded to this claim.

05:41.520 --> 05:47.540
Quote-unquote, it would have been irresponsible and unthinkable for the U.S. Air Force to jeopardize

05:47.540 --> 05:49.720
the operational status of these weapons.

05:50.360 --> 05:56.140
The EMP generator equipment would have involved a prolonged installation process in plain sight

05:56.140 --> 05:57.400
of our security team.

05:57.840 --> 06:03.000
Again, this is the same security team that expressed extreme fear to Robert Salas due to

06:03.000 --> 06:07.760
the fact that a glowing red object was hovering around the base and making right-angle turns.

06:07.860 --> 06:11.200
For whatever reason, none of this testimony made it into this article.

06:11.520 --> 06:17.540
But perhaps most damningly, I mean the real nail in the coffin for this, is that EMPs

06:17.540 --> 06:22.980
weren't even a thing until the 70s, and no documents have ever suggested that the U.S.

06:22.980 --> 06:28.260
has ever used them against our own active nuclear weapons with people in the vicinity.

06:28.260 --> 06:32.400
As my friend and journalist Merrick von Rennenkamp eloquently points out.

06:32.780 --> 06:34.280
As Merrick tweeted,

06:34.280 --> 06:39.840
Wall Street Journal is suggesting that technicians somehow moved a 60-foot science experiment

06:39.840 --> 06:46.680
up to the front gate of an alert missile facility, undetected, and then they fried the active nukes.

06:47.260 --> 06:48.440
This is a joke, right?

06:48.440 --> 06:53.040
And then you have the fact that EMPs don't usually do reversible damage.

06:53.580 --> 06:55.820
They take out all electronics in their vicinity.

06:56.420 --> 06:58.140
These missiles came back online.

06:58.560 --> 07:02.240
Maybe you could argue that EMPs can at times cause temporary downtime,

07:02.720 --> 07:08.680
but we definitely didn't have the ability to use EMPs this precisely before they were even operational.

07:09.160 --> 07:14.080
That's an insane claim that I don't even think the Wall Street Journal would pretend to defend.

07:14.080 --> 07:20.280
There are literally no logs or records anywhere from Malmstrom or any employees of that base

07:20.280 --> 07:23.080
saying these missiles didn't come back online.

07:23.460 --> 07:27.440
So they didn't just take out 10 missiles with an EMP and then turn them back on.

07:27.840 --> 07:33.280
That's extremely basic physics that Sean Kirkpatrick, a supposed physicist and the head of Arrow,

07:33.520 --> 07:35.780
the All Domain Anomalies Resolution Office,

07:36.200 --> 07:39.740
who clearly spoon-fed all of this bad information to Joel Schechtman,

07:40.120 --> 07:43.180
a man who needs to up his fact-checking game, should know.

07:43.180 --> 07:45.740
Get up, you lazy little bitches! Get up!

07:45.820 --> 07:46.420
Get up!

07:46.520 --> 07:47.120
